	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=120950><span id=Sage>Qzet</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>72 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.37]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>A good secret to keep in mind is that you want to sell your arrows back to the merchants anfter you make them. Also consider getting yourself some Charisma gear...can get bracers of +7 cha for about 50p each and as you try to advance your fletching you will get better prices buying and selling your arrows and components. At around skill 180-185 in fletching I had cha of about 90 and was able to actually make money making arrows and selling back to the merchants. I can fly thru a stack of arrows pretty fast so I was abale to make abou 60-75p per hour making arrows at that point. Thats a good way to recoup some of the investment you've put into your fletching skill to that point. Good luck there.<br><br>Also I tried the Trueshot 13 times in a row at fletching skill 135-145 and after putting in a little extra time at the fetching kit and raising my skill over 160 I succeded on the 1st try and 2 previous attempts since then. So Instead of running all over to get the goods to try and try to assemble the fabled bow just pour your plat into buying fletching goods and raise your skill.<br>This will save you a lot of grief and time..<br><br><br><br>Fletcher Skill 201....<br>Anyone need a Shaped Darkwood Compound?<br>I know someone who can make it =)</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Qzet Forestmyst<br>Hunter of 65 scars<br>New Dawnings Guild<br>Fennin Ro<br>www.newdawnings.org<br>"Beauty is in the eye of the Swordholder"</td></tr>
